 {"id":"br-r37-c1-01","title":"REVIEW: [HIGH] condensation used wrong SCC labeling (source-first instead of sink-first)","description":"fnx.condensation(G) labeled SCCs via the Rust _condensation_raw internal order, which numbered source SCCs first. nx numbers SCCs in strongly_connected_components() order (sinks first). Consequence: C.graph['mapping'], C.nodes[i]['members'], and condensation edges had integer labels flipped relative to networkx, silently breaking downstream code that indexes SCCs by label. Fixed by rebuilding condensation on top of fnx's own strongly_connected_components iterator so labels stay bit-compatible.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","updated_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","close_reason":"Fixed: condensation now iterates strongly_connected_components(G) and assigns indices in emission order, matching networkx's convention. Tested on 5-node 2-SCC DAG; mapping, edges, and members all match nx exactly; scc= arg path and empty-graph path also match.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-02","title":"REVIEW: [MEDIUM] node_connectivity on MultiGraph with parallel edges returned simple-graph value","description":"fnx.node_connectivity(MultiGraph) called into _raw_node_connectivity which collapses parallel edges. On e.g. K3 with extra parallel edges between two pairs, networkx returns min-degree=3 (parallel edges inflate the degree bound) while fnx returned 2 (simple-graph κ=n−1). Fixed by delegating multigraph inputs to networkx to preserve parity. Simple Graph/DiGraph continue to use the Rust fast path.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","updated_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","close_reason":"Fixed: node_connectivity now delegates when G.is_multigraph(). Verified on K3-parallel, K3 MG no-parallel, MDG with parallel edges — all match nx.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-03","title":"REVIEW: [MEDIUM] edge_connectivity returned float and ignored MultiGraph parallel edges","description":"Two related defects in edge_connectivity: (1) simple Graph path returned a float (e.g. 2.0) via the max-flow pipeline while nx returns an int cardinality (2). (2) MultiGraph path collapsed parallel edges: on K3 with extra parallel edges fnx returned 2.0 vs nx's 3. Fixed by coercing int-valued floats to int before returning, and delegating multigraph inputs to networkx.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","updated_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","close_reason":"Fixed: MG/MDG delegate to nx; simple Graph path casts integral float back to int. Verified across K3 simple, DG, MG with/without parallel, MDG — all match nx in value and type.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id":"br-r37-c1-0zdk4","title":"parity: is_minimal_d_separator missing kwargs + generate_random_paths weight default mismatch","description":"Two remaining real signature defects: (1) is_minimal_d_separator(G, x, y, z) — fnx is missing the keyword-only included=None, restricted=None kwargs that nx accepts; users who pass them get TypeError. (2) generate_random_paths(G, sample_size, ..., weight=None, ...) — fnx default is None but nx default is weight, which causes sampled paths to ignore weights by default in fnx. Fix is_minimal_d_separator by routing through nx via _call_networkx_for_parity (mirrors find_minimal_d_separator fix in br-71glx). Fix generate_random_paths by changing weight default to weight to match nx.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T03:42:48.730698907Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T03:45:44.285196884Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T03:45:44.283320593Z","close_reason":"Fixed in commit a5021c0. is_minimal_d_separator now accepts keyword-only included/restricted (delegates to nx for non-default cases). The bead's second sub-defect (generate_random_paths weight default) was already fixed in commit 6f21573 under bead yrj7i. 6 parity tests freeze the contract.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"br-r37-c1-0zdk4","title":"parity: is_minimal_d_separator missing kwargs + generate_random_paths weight default mismatch","description":"Two remaining real signature defects: (1) is_minimal_d_separator(G, x, y, z) — fnx is missing the keyword-only included=None, restricted=None kwargs that nx accepts; users who pass them get TypeError. (2) generate_random_paths(G, sample_size, ..., weight=None, ...) — fnx default is None but nx default is weight, which causes sampled paths to ignore weights by default in fnx. Fix is_minimal_d_separator by routing through nx via _call_networkx_for_parity (mirrors find_minimal_d_separator fix in br-71glx). Fix generate_random_paths by changing weight default to weight to match nx.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T03:42:48.730698907Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T03:48:50.016564846Z","close_reason":"Fixed in commit a5021c0. is_minimal_d_separator now accepts keyword-only included/restricted (delegates to nx for non-default cases). The bead's second sub-defect (generate_random_paths weight default) was already fixed in commit 6f21573 under bead yrj7i. 6 parity tests freeze the contract.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-19x8x","title":"parity: ISMAGS class missing from isomorphism API","description":"NetworkX exposes networkx.algorithms.isomorphism.ISMAGS(graph, subgraph, node_match=None, edge_match=None, cache=None) with is_isomorphic(), isomorphisms_iter(), subgraph_is_isomorphic(), subgraph_isomorphisms_iter(), and largest_common_subgraph(). FrankenNetworkX does not export ISMAGS. Add an ISMAGS wrapper that converts FrankenNetworkX graph objects via _networkx_graph_for_parity and delegates to NetworkX, plus parity tests for constructor signature and core methods.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T09:25:45.112099160Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T09:30:32.434165705Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T09:30:32.432309961Z","close_reason":"Completed in 2c0f4aa","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-5nop9","title":"parity: bfs_labeled_edges public signature should be (G, sources) matching networkx","description":"fnx.bfs_labeled_edges has signature (G, sources=None, sort_neighbors=None, *, source=None) — three problems vs nx (G, sources): sources is required in nx but optional here, sort_neighbors is not part of upstream signature, source is a keyword-only legacy alias. Even though both shapes appear to function, the public signature divergence is observable via inspect.signature, breaks parameter introspection used by typed wrappers, and means typer-style strict argument routing breaks. Tighten the wrapper to (G, sources) matching nx; if downstream callers pass sort_neighbors/source those are unsupported by nx and should fail loudly.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T01:09:39.386409859Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T03:16:47.912406594Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T03:16:47.910554548Z","close_reason":"Shipped in bf5195e: bfs_labeled_edges sig tightened to (G, sources). Removed sort_neighbors and source= legacy params. 3 existing tests still pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-5q77h","title":"parity: bipartite matching/cluster/basic/redundancy wrappers missing (12 functions)","description":"networkx.algorithms.bipartite exposes 12 functions not surfaced by franken_networkx: matching family (eppstein_matching, maximum_matching, minimum_weight_full_matching, to_vertex_cover), cluster family (cc_dot, cc_max, cc_min, latapy_clustering, robins_alexander_clustering), basic (degrees, sets), and redundancy (node_redundancy). Add Python wrappers in __init__.py via a new _call_networkx_bipartite_for_parity helper, export at top-level, add to __all__ under bipartite section.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T20:04:07.582914231Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T20:21:47.577934437Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T20:21:47.575865893Z","close_reason":"Shipped in f6a631a: 12 bipartite wrappers via _call_networkx_bipartite_for_parity helper (cc_dot/cc_max/cc_min routed through nx.algorithms.bipartite.cluster). All verified against nx on K33 + weighted 3x3 bipartite graph.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
